BR_text.BRsummary: The CLI 'bentoml delete' deletes the saved bundle, but shows an error message
BR_text.BRdescription:
Describe the bug
 I'm testing BentoML connected the S3-like service.
 $ bentoml list
 BENTO_SERVICE                         AGE                           APIS                       ARTIFACTS
 IrisClassifier:20200519220101_721D08  56.55 seconds                 predict<DataframeHandler>  model<SklearnModelArtifact>, test_list<PickleArtifact>
 IrisClassifier:20200519214443_46F9DD  17 minutes and 14.65 seconds  predict<DataframeHandler>  model<SklearnModelArtifact>, test_list<PickleArtifact>
 When I tries to call bentoml delete IrisClassifier:20200519214443_46F9DD, the command showed me an error message.
 $ bentoml delete -y IrisClassifier:20200519214443_46F9DD
 Failed to delete Bento IrisClassifier:20200519214443_46F9DD INTERNAL:
 BentoService IrisClassifier:20200519214443_46F9DD deleted
 However, the  disappeared on the Yatai UI.
 <denchmark-link:https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3915543/82329949-15e0bb00-9a1d-11ea-9ec2-f17ad7ed1c64.png></denchmark-link>
 
 It also disappeared from our S3-like service.
 <denchmark-link:https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3915543/82329945-137e6100-9a1d-11ea-896a-56699e9b6252.png></denchmark-link>
 
 The deletion itself seems to have been successful. But why do I get an error message like that?
 Expected behavior
 The CLI bentoml delete should not show an error message.
 Environment:
 
 OS: MacOS Catalina 10.15.4
 Python/BentoML Version : Python 3.6.10 / BentoML-0.7.7
 
 Additional context
 N/A
